The paper presents an end-to-end image compression system based on compressive sensing, which involves signal processing and information theory (cs.IT), computer vision (cs.CV), multimedia (cs.MM), machine learning (cs.LG), and potentially hardware design (cs.AR). However, since the focus is on the compression performance and optimization, cs.IT and cs.CV are the most likely sub-categories. The use of quantization and entropy coding also suggests a connection to information theory. The mention of the compressive sensing camera also implies a potential application in hardware design.
